Subject: LM Studio Corpus Prompt Evidence Review 013

Description: Diversified LM Studio worker prompt packet for evidence review.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_lmstudio_second_corpus_launch_queue\Derived_LMStudio_Second_Corpus_Launch_Queue_Source.sop

& [LMStudioCorpusPrompt:evidence_review_013] is a non-mutating SOP worker prompt packet
  + [task_family] is evidence_review
  + [prompt_boundary] is prompt-only, no tools, no file reads, no repo mutation, no hidden-state claims
  + [expected_output] is exactly one raw SOP node named InferenceJobResult with seven property lines and no Markdown
  + [validation_required_fields] is capture, evidence, outside, integration_status, caution, revise, next_step
  + [validation_required_terms] is capture, evidence, outside, not integrated, revise
  + [validation_forbidden_terms] is approved, verified, proof complete, hidden state accessed
  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    Evidence review separates a captured worker claim from proof, outside, caution, revision, and integration status.

    Task family:
    evidence_review tests whether you can critique a weak worker claim, identify missing proof, preserve outside, and propose a revision without integrating it.

    Capture to review:
    "The worker says the local model is ready for all SOP jobs because it passed one isolated prompt."

    Return exactly these eight raw SOP lines and no extra text:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is evidence review proposal
      + [capture] is ...
      + [evidence] is ...
      + [outside] is ...
      + [integration_status] is ...
      + [caution] is ...
      + [revise] is ...
      + [next_step] is ...

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 8 must use exactly this operator form: two spaces, +, space, [field], space, is, space, value.
    Do not replace is with verbs such as includes, separates, reminds, lists, or contains.
    Replace every ... placeholder with specific content; do not output ellipses or placeholder text.
    Use ASCII only; avoid curly quotes, nonbreaking hyphens, and special punctuation.
    Include the literal terms capture, evidence, outside, not integrated, and revise at least once.
    Do not claim approved, verified, proof complete, or hidden state accessed.
